An Indonesian lawyer for condemned Bali Nine duo Andrew Chan and Myuran Sukumaran has tried to enlist the support of heavy metal band Metallica in an attempt to get mercy for the pair.

Indonesian President Joko Widodo is a known fan of the rockers, and on Sunday morning lawyer Todung Mulya Lubis made the unusual appeal to the band via social media.

'Hello @Metallica? You have to campaign to save life in Indonesia from Death Penalty. Come, sing and make plea to @jokowi_do2 (the president)', he posted to his Twitter account.

Mr Lubis also wrote a follow up tweet, sending a YouTube link to Metallica telling the band 'the whole world is watching'. 

