The plea from the Bali Nine duo's lawyers to Metallica is not the first time a heavy metal band has been involved in the case, it is widely known that Widodo is a big fan of heavy metal.

Earlier this year a British band known as one of the Indonesian President's favourites penned a letter to Joko Widodo asking him to grant clemency to Australian convicted drug traffickers Andrew Chan and Myruan Sukumaran.

Mr Widodo is said to be a big fan of metal, and recently revealed in an interview that he discovered the genre when he stumbled across a thrash metal band gig when he was just 14 years old.

Knowing he was a fan of the band, Napalm Death's lead singer Mark 'Barney' Greenway posted the open letter addressed to Mr Widodo to the band's Facebook page in January, for their 729,000 followers to read.

